('Aaron Sookram', 'Aaron', 'Sookram', 'Proven Hospitality Leader: Sale/Revenue Management      
Brand Marketing I Event Planner I Guest Experience I', 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/aaron-sookram', 'aaron-sookram', $${"about": "I am a hospitality leader with a passion for customer service and travel.\n\nWith over five years in the industry, I am well versed in leadership, strategic planning, and administration of hotel operations.\n\nI graduated from Florida State University with a BA in Hospitality Management and humbly began my career as a line cook and night shift auditor. Through this, I gradually built my career and now hold a managerial role at Bed Station Hotel, a reputable hotel/hostel chain in Bangkok, Thailand.\n\nI am a hands-on leader and excel in key roles such as:\n-Budget and revenue administration\n-Community management\n-Event planning and organization \n-Staff management\n\nI am currently open to any long-term roles at a global hospitality chain, F&B establishment, and nightlife industry that will further my career.  \n\nEmail: sookramaaron@gmail.com", "addressCountryOnly": "Thailand", "addressWithCountry": "Bangkok City, Thailand", "addressWithoutCountry": "Bangkok City", "backgroundPic": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C5616AQH5rJfPEJikng/profile-displaybackgroundimage-shrink_350_1400/profile-displaybackgroundimage-shrink_350_1400/0/1599606368585?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=JeV-hPOuFWWQY5iMvkdjfjGg7QsHkuOhe4xHYE1v_U8", "companyName": "Bed Station Group (Khaosan)", "connections": "227", "currentJobDuration": "7 yrs 9 mos", "currentJobDurationInYrs": "7.75", "educations/0/companyId": "18100", "educations/0/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/school/florida-state-university/", "educations/0/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:18100", "educations/0/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQHa2RFLI1581g/company-logo_400_400/B4EZueFnoXLYAY-/0/1767883832111/florida_state_university_logo?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=vXedAjN9dkQlUhQN4tqH5x6NrS14qoguakDVXeXObG8", "educations/0/period/endedOn/month": "0", "educations/0/period/endedOn/year": "2012", "educations/0/period/startedOn/month": "0", "educations/0/period/startedOn/year": "2007", "educations/0/subtitle": "Bachelor of Arts - BA, Hospitality Administration/Management", "educations/0/title": "Florida State University", "experiences/0/companyName": "Bed Station Group (Khaosan)", "experiences/0/employmentType": "Full-time", "experiences/0/jobDescription": "Bed Station Group has a collection of hotels and hostels in Southeast Asia. The chain's Khaosarn branch is one of the largest properties in its portfolio, located in the heart of Bangkok's tourist hub, Khaosan Road.\n\nFrom the early stages, I was actively involved in the process of the opening of the hotel. During my tenure, I directly oversaw both the F&B and front office operations.\n\nOver the years, I implemented a vast amount of procedures in the F&B department to operate more efficiently, thus resulting in a higher revenue yield. As Assistant General Manager, I developed new strategies and sales techniques to help reduce operational costs of the hotel/hostel's front desk and increase the overall revenue stream. To ensure that the changes were implemented properly I headed staff training and oversaw the operational changes. As a result of these improvements, the hotel reached record highs in revenue, outperforming all the branches in Asia.\n\nDuring the COVID period, I created new protocols on the check-in/check-out procedure to help reduce the risk of infection to our guests and staff. I organized an information-group for guests to ensure that they had 24/7 access to the latest airline/flight updates while stranded in Thailand during COVID, and provided assistance to those wishing to stay in Asia with visa advice, finding new accommodation, and other travel advice.\n   \n\n\n\n\nResponsibilities: \n\n-Provide effective leadership to hotel team members.\n-Deliver hotel budget goals and set other short and long term strategic goals for the property.\n-Prepare monthly financial reports for the owners. \n-Oversee and manage all departments and work closely with department heads on a daily basis.\n-Ensure that monthly financial outlooks for rooms, F&B, admin, and general management are on target and accurate.\n-Handle complaints, and oversee the service recovery procedures.", "experiences/0/jobLocation": "Bangkok City, Thailand", "experiences/0/jobStartedOn": "8-2018", "experiences/0/jobStillWorking": "true", "experiences/0/title": "Founding Assistant General Manager", "experiences/1/companyId": "67450316", "experiences/1/companyIndustry": "Restaurants", "experiences/1/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/brooklyn-depot-south/", "experiences/1/companyName": "BROOKLYN DEPOT SOUTH", "experiences/1/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:67450316", "experiences/1/companyWebsite": "http://brooklyndepotsouthbank.com", "experiences/1/employmentType": "Full-time", "experiences/1/jobDescription": "Brooklyn Depot is an American bistro with a hint of Aussie flare, specializing in classical American comfort food in the heart of Melbourne's CBD. As an American trained chef, I was able to ensure the authenticity of the restaurant's cuisine and innovate classic American favorites.  \n\n\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n-Effectively coordinated with daily operations, directed staff, and oversaw finances and inventory. \n-Created a staff schedule and encouraged high levels of performance.\n- Installed procedures to reduce food costs by 5%, simultaneously boosting revenue by 6% year-to-year.", "experiences/1/jobEndedOn": "8-2018", "experiences/1/jobLocation": "Melbourne, Victoria, Australia", "experiences/1/jobStartedOn": "8-2017", "experiences/1/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/1/title": "Chef", "experiences/2/companyId": "6682987", "experiences/2/companyIndustry": "Food and Beverage Services", "experiences/2/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/tampa-bay-brewing-company/", "experiences/2/companyName": "Tampa Bay Brewing Company", "experiences/2/companySize": "51-2